I recognize your "STS Engineer" badge, but I have serious doubts of your legitimacy. And I like the compositions of Beethoven as much as I'd like the composition of a sandwich made of ingredients from a landfill.

Overall, I would rate this seven out of ten, the same rating I would give to a New York strip cooked medium-rare instead of my usual medium-well. It is flanked by bacon, my rating being a six out of ten (or 5.5 if rounding is not applied), and a well-cooked spaghetti dish with just the right marinara sauce being an eight out of ten.
